01:02.401 --> 01:04.200
aah!

01:04.202 --> 01:07.395
"A scream pierced the air,

01:07.515 --> 01:10.372
falling only on the
deaf ears of the dead."

01:11.550 --> 01:13.474
Really? A little too over the top?

01:13.839 --> 01:15.448
I think I've been writing too long

01:15.738 --> 01:18.329
not to know that it's "I"
before "E" except after "C."

01:18.746 --> 01:20.613
Ever heard of spell-check?
Yes, of course.

01:20.614 --> 01:22.680
She's got red hair,
she's wise beyond her years,

01:22.681 --> 01:24.615
and she's about to tell
her dad what she thinks

01:24.616 --> 01:26.002
of the latest chapter
of his new book.

01:26.239 --> 01:27.701
I loved it, especially the part

01:27.821 --> 01:29.537
with Nikki and Rook in
the aircraft carrier.

01:30.164 --> 01:32.258
Awesome. Stop it.
You're embarrassing me.

01:32.749 --> 01:34.035
I do have one note, though.

01:34.155 --> 01:36.804
This new character, the,
uh, robbery Detective...

01:37.158 --> 01:38.594
Schlemming. What about him?

01:38.922 --> 01:41.092
Well, he seems like he kinda
came up out of nowhere.

01:41.093 --> 01:42.496
Yeah, well,
I can't argue with that.

01:42.842 --> 01:44.511
He's coming off a
bit like a doofus.

01:44.631 --> 01:45.643
You think?

01:45.763 --> 01:47.045
I think you should lose him.

01:47.732 --> 01:50.059
If only it was this easy.

01:51.096 --> 01:52.284
Thank you for your help, sweetie.

01:52.404 --> 01:53.521
I am so behind on my deadline.

01:53.641 --> 01:55.565
That's 'cause you always find
new ways to procrastinate.

01:57.387 --> 01:58.879
Or they find me. Hello, mother.

01:59.570 --> 02:01.541
Oh, hi, guys. I can't stay.

02:01.542 --> 02:02.887
I'm just picking up a dress.

02:03.007 --> 02:05.033
Chet's taking me to the
theater this evening.

02:05.287 --> 02:06.358
Oh, what are you seeing?

02:06.478 --> 02:09.213
New Petrofsky play,
"Edge of Awakening."

02:09.214 --> 02:10.608
Wait a minute.
Didn't you audition for that?

02:10.728 --> 02:11.829
Uh-huh, yes.

02:11.949 --> 02:14.250
And that wonderful actress
Madge Vance got my part,

02:14.251 --> 02:15.783
the way she usually does.

02:15.903 --> 02:17.151
Well, she's not even
really your friend.

02:17.271 --> 02:18.956
It's nice that you go
and support her. I know.

02:19.076 --> 02:21.517
And... I have to go soon,
because it's closing.

02:21.637 --> 02:24.032
The critics are saying it's a...
"train wreck."

02:24.152 --> 02:26.203
Oh, there's the
Martha Rodgers I know.

02:27.939 --> 02:29.201
Ah, Beckett.

02:29.712 --> 02:31.072
Please tell me there's
been a murder,

02:31.192 --> 02:32.416
otherwise, I'll have
to continue writing.

02:39.986 --> 02:41.654
People always say they
want to die in their sleep.

02:41.774 --> 02:44.100
What you want is a good,
clean shot to take you out

02:44.220 --> 02:46.648
before you know what hit you.
Not this poor guy.

02:47.672 --> 02:50.273
Bullet missed the heart.
He didn't die for quite a while.

02:50.393 --> 02:51.679
Looks like he was

02:51.799 --> 02:52.706
reaching for the phone
to call for help.

02:52.826 --> 02:55.391
Until our doer took
<i>that</i> to his head.

02:56.310 --> 02:57.578
Probably didn't want to risk

02:57.579 --> 02:59.065
the neighbors hearing
a second shot,

02:59.185 --> 03:01.235
and so he grabbed the nearest
thing and finished him off.

03:02.082 --> 03:04.224
There's blood splatter on the clock--
must have been

03:04.344 --> 03:05.850
knocked off the nightstand
during the attack.

03:05.970 --> 03:08.553
10:34. At least we know what time

03:08.554 --> 03:09.793
the festivities started.

03:09.913 --> 03:10.922
There's no signs of forced entry.

03:11.042 --> 03:12.256
He probably left this open

03:12.257 --> 03:13.558
so he could get a
breath of fresh air.

03:14.243 --> 03:16.324
And there's no security
cameras either.

03:16.796 --> 03:18.488
And I didn't see any
on the way in. Mm.

03:18.608 --> 03:19.882
Cleaning lady found
him this morning.

03:20.002 --> 03:21.740
She said that usually,
Wilder would've left for work

03:21.860 --> 03:23.920
by the time she got here.
Wilder? Damian Wilder?

03:24.389 --> 03:26.157
Yeah, you know him? I know <i>of</i> him.

03:26.537 --> 03:28.566
This is a photo from one
of his ad campaigns.

03:28.686 --> 03:31.825
He--he runs a line of boutique
men's skincare products.

03:31.945 --> 03:33.474
You mean, like, bathroom stuff?

03:33.475 --> 03:35.409
He has got a toner,
totally alcohol-free,

03:35.410 --> 03:36.943
fantastic.

03:36.944 --> 03:39.230
He's got a shaving cream
that is ridiculous.

03:39.546 --> 03:41.043
I'm good with the
drug store stuff, man.

03:41.163 --> 03:42.129
No, no, no, no, no. Hang on.

03:42.249 --> 03:44.216
This stuff will change your life.

03:44.217 --> 03:45.684
It's hot. It's hot.

03:45.685 --> 03:47.518
It's hot? It's hot.

03:47.519 --> 03:49.361
It's hot. How do they do that?

03:49.481 --> 03:50.768
Magic of modern chemistry.

03:50.888 --> 03:52.822
It's like getting a
shave from a barber.

03:52.823 --> 03:55.668
Matter of fact, that's the tagline-
-barber in a can. Huh.

03:55.788 --> 03:56.973
So it's probably expensive, huh?

03:57.093 --> 03:58.872
It's 50 bucks a pop,
but it's so worth it.

03:59.176 --> 04:00.195
Absolutely. Totally. Yeah.

04:00.196 --> 04:02.864
Guys... a man has
been murdered here.

04:02.865 --> 04:05.662
And we are... honoring his legacy.

04:05.929 --> 04:08.247
Mm. It's like "Sex and the City,"

04:08.367 --> 04:09.628
only with boys.

04:09.907 --> 04:11.438
Maybe you guys can check
in with the neighbors,

04:11.439 --> 04:13.507
see if they saw or heard anything?

04:13.508 --> 04:15.042
Oh, yeah. All over it.

04:15.043 --> 04:17.543
Yeah, I'm on it. Come on, Castle.
Let me show you what I found.

04:21.262 --> 04:23.126
Something was stolen
from these cases.

04:23.885 --> 04:25.719
Hmm. Those are humidity controls.

04:26.138 --> 04:27.906
Well, whatever it was
was very valuable,

04:28.026 --> 04:29.722
because the killer
passed up the plasma tv

04:29.723 --> 04:31.189
and the blu-ray player.

04:31.190 --> 04:33.007
Robbery gone wrong?

04:33.438 --> 04:34.538
Looks that way, doesn't it?

04:35.070 --> 04:37.027
And then there's this.

04:39.256 --> 04:41.031
Is that an "E" or an "O"?

04:41.701 --> 04:43.067
"Murdero," is that
Spanish for murder?

04:43.068 --> 04:45.535
"Murdere." The killer was French.

04:45.536 --> 04:46.978
The thing I don't get about it

04:47.098 --> 04:48.942
is why would a thief take the time

04:49.062 --> 04:51.122
to write a message out
of our vic's blood?

04:51.388 --> 04:53.775
Especially that message.
I mean, we know it's murder.

04:53.776 --> 04:55.211
The dead body's kind of a giveaway.

04:55.705 --> 04:56.691
So we're still canvassing,

04:56.811 --> 04:58.953
but I thought you'd want
to hear this--neighbor said

04:59.073 --> 05:00.945
she was on her treadmill last
night listening to music.

05:01.065 --> 05:02.331
So she didn't hear the shot.

05:02.451 --> 05:04.385
No, but she did open her
back door to let the cat in,

05:04.386 --> 05:06.308
and she saw someone
hopping over the fence

05:06.428 --> 05:07.641
on their way out of Wilder's yard.

05:07.761 --> 05:08.657
You get a description?

05:08.777 --> 05:10.940
Yeah, "a foot disappearing
over the fence."

05:11.060 --> 05:12.274
Did you get a time at all?

05:12.394 --> 05:14.041
10:52 on the button.
It was still on her alarm box.

05:14.161 --> 05:16.095
She forget she'd set it
when she opened the door.

05:16.096 --> 05:18.797
So now we know what time last
night's festivities ended.

05:18.798 --> 05:19.769
10:52.

05:19.889 --> 05:21.667
All right, have C.S.U.
sweep for prints and fibers

05:21.787 --> 05:22.981
and make sure they hit
the backyard as well.

05:23.101 --> 05:24.060
You got it.

05:37.941 --> 05:38.908
Demming.

05:39.206 --> 05:40.275
Castle.

05:44.617 --> 05:47.055
You guys use, uh,
boards down in robbery?

05:47.638 --> 05:48.982
Sure, yeah.

05:50.172 --> 05:51.465
Well, come back tomorrow.

05:51.585 --> 05:53.886
It'll be full of all
sorts of murder-y stuff.

05:54.122 --> 05:56.956
Beckett asked me to assist
in the investigation, so...

05:56.957 --> 05:57.885
Really?

05:58.273 --> 05:59.772
Yeah, because of the
robbery component.

06:00.086 --> 06:01.359
Of course.

06:01.752 --> 06:04.052
I tracked down Wilder's next of kin,
his cousin Blake.

06:04.274 --> 06:05.623
He's in the interview lounge.

06:09.066 --> 06:11.967
You know how he got in the
business he did? Acne.

06:12.500 --> 06:14.870
As a teenager,
he had it something terrible.

06:14.871 --> 06:16.656
When he asked me to lend him
money to start up a business,

06:16.776 --> 06:19.346
I was happy to do it. He...

06:19.967 --> 06:22.062
He was one of the good ones.

06:22.302 --> 06:25.931
I mean, why somebody would do
something like this, I... mm.

06:26.856 --> 06:28.238
Blake,

06:28.606 --> 06:30.450
we were hoping that you could
help us with something.

06:30.451 --> 06:32.385
The display cases
in the living room

06:32.386 --> 06:34.521
were broken into and their
contents were missing.

06:34.522 --> 06:36.455
Well, that's where
he kept his books.

06:36.456 --> 06:38.323
He was a collector-
rare printings,

06:38.324 --> 06:40.258
signed first editions,
things like that.

06:40.259 --> 06:41.878
Those could run into the thousands,

06:41.998 --> 06:44.830
even tens of thousands.
So it was robbery?

06:44.831 --> 06:46.898
Somebody killed him
to take his books?

06:46.899 --> 06:48.405
Well, it's possible
there's another motive.

06:48.525 --> 06:49.902
We found a message
written on the wall.

06:50.586 --> 06:51.539
That's odd.

06:51.659 --> 06:53.871
We're still working on that.
What we could really use

06:53.872 --> 06:55.840
your help on is with
the missing books.

06:55.841 --> 06:57.553
Did he have a catalog
of his collection?

06:57.673 --> 06:59.018
Sure. Damian looked to me

06:59.138 --> 07:00.911
to help him out with the
business side of things.

07:00.912 --> 07:02.371
The insurer he used
is a friend of mine.

07:02.491 --> 07:04.170
He'll have a catalog.
Well, as far as we know,

07:04.290 --> 07:06.431
the only thing missing were
the books, which suggests

07:06.551 --> 07:08.453
the perpetrator went there
knowing what he was looking for.

07:08.757 --> 07:10.735
Could be he had an opportunity
to case the apartment.

07:11.026 --> 07:11.860
Well, the kitchen--

07:11.980 --> 07:13.921
I mean, Damian had the
entire thing renovated.

07:14.327 --> 07:16.606
The place was crawling
with workers for weeks.

07:18.246 --> 07:20.210
Killed for a fortune
in stolen books.

07:20.863 --> 07:23.421
So I'll run the work crews and
see if anybody has priors.

07:23.967 --> 07:25.523
Thanks, Tom. I appreciate
your help on this.

07:25.865 --> 07:27.137
I'll let you know if
anything turns up.

07:30.422 --> 07:32.161
I'm not sure why everybody's
jumping to the conclusion

07:32.281 --> 07:33.609
that this murder was
about the stolen books.

07:33.610 --> 07:35.510
Maybe because they're missing.

07:35.879 --> 07:38.413
The message on the mirror
suggests an intention to kill,

07:38.414 --> 07:40.189
a motive of some kind.

07:40.658 --> 07:43.216
Stealing books-
just a crime of opportunity.

07:43.217 --> 07:45.485
And now who's jumping
to conclusions?

07:45.486 --> 07:47.947
I just hate to see
anybody waste their time.

07:48.378 --> 07:50.589
The key here is the message,
not the books.

07:50.907 --> 07:53.293
I think we should pursue
both lines of investigation.

07:53.521 --> 07:55.893
Well, he's your boyfriend.
Excuse me?

07:55.894 --> 07:58.162
I'm sorry. Am I jumping
to conclusions again?

07:58.163 --> 07:59.697
It's none of your business.

08:00.362 --> 08:01.784
Yo.

08:02.544 --> 08:04.367
Ran a background check on Wilder.

08:04.813 --> 08:05.868
Found this incident report

08:05.869 --> 08:07.904
that he filed with the
police three days ago.

08:07.905 --> 08:09.338
Somebody vandalized his apartment.

08:09.544 --> 08:11.232
Poured red paint
all over his stoop.

08:11.465 --> 08:14.077
Yeah, it turns out that, uh,
his company was being picketed

08:14.078 --> 08:15.712
by animal rights protestors.

08:15.713 --> 08:17.814
But all of his stuff is labeled "
no animal testing."

08:17.815 --> 08:20.133
The problem was with, uh,
one of his subcontractors,

08:20.253 --> 08:21.923
who was doing some of the
manufacturing for him.

08:22.515 --> 08:23.736
Wilder didn't even know about it.

08:24.355 --> 08:25.700
That's what the message was.

08:27.440 --> 08:28.932
It wasn't misspelled.
It was unfinished.

08:29.457 --> 08:30.823
They were writing "murderer.
" So you think

08:30.943 --> 08:33.082
that one of the animal
rights activists killed him.

08:33.203 --> 08:35.596
Sure. One of them had enough
with the fake blood, decided,

08:35.716 --> 08:37.421
"I'm gonna send a message
using the real thing."

08:37.726 --> 08:39.511
Maybe we should pay
Wilder's office a visit

08:39.727 --> 08:41.866
and find out more about
those protestors.

08:49.339 --> 08:52.619
